The TDD exercise is complete. All 6 tests pass and `experiment-done.txt` has been written.

**Summary of what was built:**

```typescript
// src/pixel-art-scaler.ts
const scaleRow = (row: string, scale: number): string =>
  row.split("").map(pixel => pixel.repeat(scale)).join("");

export const scalePixelArt = (image: string[], scale: number): string[] =>
  image.flatMap(row => Array.from({ length: scale }, () => scaleRow(row, scale)));
```

The implementation emerged through 6 Red-Green-Refactor cycles:
- Tests 1-2 (empty, scale-1) drove the basic structure
- Test 3 (single pixel block) forced both horizontal and vertical scaling
- Tests 4-6 passed immediately — confirming the implementation was already fully general
